                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.311F1 Advisory Committee/1062a:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-03T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 3, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5624. Your 5767, November 29. It is understood that Salter has telegraphed London
                    concerning our proposal referred to in paragraph 6 (prices) of Department’s 5346
                        [<hi rend="italic">5446</hi>], November 26 and has asked for instructions.
                    If you have not already done so, please advise the appropriate British
                    authorities that you are expecting instructions in this connection and suggest
                    that their reply to Salter be delayed until you have had an opportunity to
                    discuss the matter with them. In the meantime, a reply concerning the questions
                    raised in your 5767 will be sent as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
